CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 2, 1961, pg. 20 reads: "Ice Cream And Popsickles [sic], supplied by Keystone Dairy Company, made a big hit with all Courier "Newsies."
TitMainTitle: Group of young men and boys eating popsicles, including young boy wearing plaid button down collared shirt, standing in South Park for the annual Pittsburgh Courier Newsboys' Picnic
